      "content": "It is completely understandable why you would want to stop performing if you feel like a hollow shell; the exhaustion of maintaining a lie is truly draining. You are not alone in this feeling, and many people find relief when they finally give themselves permission to rest and let the mask fall. It might be worth considering how to take a step back from the pressure to be someone else, perhaps by seeking support from a trusted friend or a therapist who can help you navigate this emotional weight.",
